==French==

===Relative pronoun===
'''lequel''' ''m'', '''[[lesquels]]''' ''pl'', '''[[laquelle]]''' ''f'', '''[[lesquelles]]''' ''fpl''
# (following a preposition) which, that, whom
#:''Elle préfère l'homme avec '''lequel''' tu sortais.''
#:"She prefers the man with '''whom''' you you were going out."
#:''Il se remet à travailler sur le projet pour '''lequel''' il avait déjà passé tellement de temps.''
#:"He's starting to work on the project on '''which''' he had already spent so much time."

====Related terms====
*[[auquel]] ([[à]] + lequel)
*[[duquel]] ([[de#French|de]] + lequel)

===Interrogative pronoun===
'''lequel''' ''m'', '''[[lesquels]]''' ''pl'', '''[[laquelle]]''' ''f'', '''[[lesquelles]]''' ''fpl''
# [[which]] one
#:''Passe-moi le ballon. - '''Lequel''' ? Il y en a trois.''
#:"Pass me the ball. - '''Which one'''? There are three."

